{
  "texts": [
    "4, 5 So, as VIR techniques and procedures mature and achieve wider acceptance, it could prove more useful in multidisciplinary care with the incorporation of AI potentially leading to improved outcomes for all stakeholders.",
    "6 In this context, VIR is the frontier of the concept of Imaging 3.0, an initiative aimed at showcasing the expanded contributions of radiologists beyond conventional image interpretation.",
    "7 In detailing key aspects, VIR shows its pivotal role in percutaneous, image-guided procedures such as abscess drainage and needle biopsy.",
    "This emphasizes the specialty's capacity to reduce morbidity, enhance patient outcomes, and offer cost-effective alternatives to other surgical interventions.",
    "Additionally, the significance of transjugular intrahepatic portosystemic shunts and the central role of interventional radiologists in delivering cost-effective central venous access services are emphasized, making substantial contributions to multidisciplinary cancer treatment."
  ]
}